      "date": "2014-12-01 06:20:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThe race looks was introduced on client side, current client code doesn't udpate timestamps after building RPC.\n\nAndreas, looks the server side code is correct. ofd_write/read_lock() protects the fmd lookup/update and timestamps update, and ofd_attr_write_set() does set UID/GID only as you described, the timestamps updating is always in the write transaction.",
